column4: Plaintiffs in Microsoft sex bias case fight to keep suit alive
column5: A proposed class action claiming Microsoft Corp systematically discriminated against female employees in pay and promotions adequately alleges that the company's performance review system was designed to favor men  lawyers for the plaintiffs told a U.S. judge.

column4: Tesla says Australian utility Origin to market solar battery
column5: SYDNEY Tesla Motors Inc  on Thursday listed Australia's largest power and gas retailer Origin Energy  as one of the distributors for its solar battery storage product which the company is launching globally in two other countries.

column4: UPDATE 1-Tesla says Australian utility Origin to market solar battery

column4: Tesla says Australian utility Origin to market solar battery
column5: SYDNEY  Dec 10 Tesla Motors Inc on Thursday listed Australia's largest power and gas retailer Origin Energy as one of the distributors for its solar battery storage product which the company is launching globally in two other countries.

column4: Philips in lighting partnerships with Cisco  SAP and Bosch
column5: AMSTERDAM Philips  has entered strategic partnerships with Cisco   SAP  and Bosch [ROBG.UL] under which each will jointly market networking systems using Philips programmable lights.

column4: UPDATE 3-Philips in lighting partnerships with Cisco  SAP and Bosch
column5: * Philips estimates office lighting market at 1 bln euros a year   (Recasts first paragraph to clarify deals are partnerships  not supply deals)

column4: Philips in lighting partnerships with Cisco  SAP and Bosch
column5: AMSTERDAM  Dec 9 Philips has entered strategic partnerships with Cisco  SAP and Bosch  under which the Dutch company will become a preferred supplier of networked lights.
